Subject: RE: [VB] Front brake drum seal problem, etc.

oh yeah, a 68-- seal has a different inside diameter, so you'd need the
"adapter" sized seal.


> [Original Message]
> yes, i've seen this before. i believe you have a 68-70 front drum, which
> will work on a split. you need to get the "adapter" seal that has the same
> inside diameter as the early, but the outside diameter as the late drum. i
> don't have a part number, but i know foreign aide in albuquerque
> (1-800-658-5712) stocks them (if you describe the early/late drum scenario
> they should be able to find it on the shelf no problem--it should be with
> the 64-67 seals), and maybe ronnie does too, but i don't know for sure.
> when you get the "adapter" seal, it should bolt on no problem.
> 
> 
> > [Original Message]
> > Greetings, All...
> >     I received my new front brake drums(yea!) for my 65 and
> > proceeded to clean them up(yea!) and install new bearings(yea!).
> > Got the bearing races installed(yea!) and then went to test fit the
> > seal. The seal just dropped in...(boo!). 
> >    OK...the drums are Frum units, #1346E, =VW#211.405.615E.
> > The seals are Sabo 01711-BRG, and are supposed to be = VW#
> > 211.405.641B.(I believe they are correct for that year VW bus
> > because the new seal will fit my old drums fine).
> >    The the new drum seal bore is 1 or 2mm. larger than the old VW
> > original drums.
> >    Has anyone run into this problem and, if so, how did you correct it?
